                          batch file help exist checks clear status messages 8.3 dos-compatible names model files                                                                         Batch file help                                                 In a batch file, use IF EXIST checks, clear status messages, and 8.3 DOS-compatible names for model files.                                                                                      8.3 names dos filenames maximum compatibility predictable batch files                                                                                           DOS filenames                                                   Use 8.3 filenames for maximum DOS compatibility and predictable batch files.                                                                                                                    cwsdpmi missing protected-mode program fails start copy cwsdpmi.exe beside rerun command                                                                        Missing CWSDPMI                                                 If a protected-mode program fails to start, copy CWSDPMI.EXE beside it and rerun the command.                                                                                                   fat image full remove host-only training files grow disk assembly runs out space                                                                                FAT image full                                                  Remove host-only training files or grow the disk image when FAT image assembly runs out of space.                                                                                               memory error dos free conventional unloading tsrs loading drivers high using smaller profile                                                                    DOS memory error                                                Free conventional memory by unloading TSRs, loading drivers high, or using a smaller profile.                                                                                                   compile basic freebasic build dos executable pinned toolchain keep cwsdpmi output                                                                               FreeBASIC compile                                               Build the DOS executable with the pinned FreeBASIC toolchain and keep CWSDPMI with the output.                                                                                                  